  "@type": "Article",
  "dateModified": "2025-12-31",
  "datePublished": "2025-12-31",
  "description": "A semioverse surface is a readable interface that exposes semiotic structures through pages, links, and metadata. In the context of an Agential Semioverse Repository, the surface is the layer that renders the repository\u0026rsquo;s internal sign relations, cross-references, and typed fragments as navigable web content. An MkDocs or Quartz build produces a semioverse surface by converting Markdown files, frontmatter, and wikilinks into HTML pages with hyperlinked structure. The surface preserves the relational topology of the underlying vault while making it accessible to human readers and machine consumers.\n",
  "name": "semioverse surface",
